{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"53122e81-962e-4130-bf90-227f1daeac51","content":"The issue is classic F#: **file compilation order matters**. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on types from `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear earlier in the compilation list.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_DBFeIw6CCdnAynP2SLi2VE","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-981b22de754145fa887432280efaec19/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-981b22de754145fa887432280efaec19/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"7920a7f2-5b70-4166-955e-df9283dbb85c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the `.fsproj` file.\n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\n\nI need to reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`, which comes before `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"1C56:1BE42F:B439EA:D102C1:69F3FA0C"},"id":"1dcbbf65-c16e-4aa0-b766-27b130cdb7b7","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:48.334Z","parentId":"04004023-d4eb-4f9d-bb7e-d80c4f872fdb"}
